\layout Title

Balanced Mixer Tuner Design and Mixer Performance
\layout Date

20th January, 2004
\layout Author

Paul Grimes
\layout Section*

Introduction
\layout Standard

Simulations include Belitsky tuner with tuner mirostrip width of 
\begin_inset Formula $7.0\mu m$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $30\mu m$
\end_inset 

 radial RF choke fed by 
\begin_inset Formula $39.0\times3.0\mu m$
\end_inset 

microstrip and 
\begin_inset Formula $65fF$
\end_inset 

 inlince capacitance as a DC block.
 For each simulation the LO power was optimised for the frequency with the
 greatest gain, and the bias was set at 
\begin_inset Formula $2.0mV$
\end_inset 

.
